		<h1>Classes</h1>
		<p>
		<img alt="A flute class" src="App_Themes/Theme1/images/class.JPG" width="490" /></p>
		<p>Irish Traditional Music Classes organised by Craobh Naithí run every Thursday from
		6:00 pm to 9pm in St. Columcille's Community School, Scholarstown Road, Knocklyon for children
		from 8 years of age.   All grades from beginner to advanced pupils are catered for.</p>
        <p>Due to the demand for class places for children, Craobh Naithí regrets that we are not
        in a position to offer adult beginner classes at present.</p>
        <p>In addition, Grúpa Cheoil classes are available for all registered pupils who have a number
         of years playing experience. A number of Ceili Bands are also organised based on age group.</p> 
		<div id="full">
		<p>Classes will resume on Thursday January 12th, 2012</p>
			</div>
